\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Correlation matrix for gaussian copula
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One of the most important step in pricing Basket Default Swap is the estimation
 of the correlation matrix.
 The correlation matrix is generally obtained through historical sampling.
 Sereval ways to estimate the correlation matrix have been researched:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Difference of default probability (daily and weekly data)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Log difference of default probability (daily and weekly data)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Hazard rates (daily and weekly data)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Difference of hazard rates (daily and weekly data)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Log difference of hazard rates (daily and weekly data)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Stock return (daily)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
